{
  "text": "Polderman described the induction phase of MIH as the phase which presents the most patient management problems, such as frequent adjustments in ventilator settings and sedation dosing, insulin, vasoactive, and electrolyte replacement therapy, and should therefore be executed rapidly, so that a more stable maintenance phase is reached as quickly as possible [CITATION_1] . Infusion of 30 mL/kg of fluid cooled to at least 4\u00b0C, as recommended by the current guidelines is popular for its low costs and simplicity of usage, as it allows a successful performance of MIH in the hospital and pre-hospital environment and during complex procedures, such as primary percutaneous coronary intervention. However, despite its wide applicability, its potentials are still not used in entirety [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
